      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_SBMR_GetTheNextSBMRRefereceNumber",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate the next sequential SBMR (presumably a reference number for a specific business process) reference number. It constructs this reference number based on the current date and the last used sequence number for the current period. The procedure outputs this new reference number as a string in the format "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "YYMMNNN",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", where "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "YYMM",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " represents the year and month, and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "NNN",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a zero-padded sequence number."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving basic string manipulation and arithmetic operations. It calls another stored procedure to retrieve the last sequence number, which adds a slight layer of complexity, but overall, the logic is simple and easy to follow."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
